President Barack Obama has proclaimed May 8, 2015, as Military Spouse Appreciation Day. In his proclamation, he acknowledges the sacrifices and contributions that military spouses make in supporting their loved ones who serve in the military. The President highlights the importance of providing support and resources to military families, including mental health care, counseling, and employment opportunities. He also mentions the Joining Forces initiative, launched by First Lady Michelle Obama and Dr. Jill Biden, which aims to raise awareness about military life and ensure that military spouses have access to the opportunities and benefits they deserve. The President calls upon the people of the United States to honor military spouses on this day through appropriate ceremonies and activities.